<paragraph blockId="1.[677,1210,1473,1699]" pageId="1" pageNumber="190">
It is worth to note that the 
<typeStatus box="[939,979,1596,1620]" pageId="1" pageNumber="190">type</typeStatus>
species is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grateloup" authorityYear="1832" box="[1068,1210,1596,1620]" class="Gastropoda" family="Neritopsidae" genus="Neritopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cycloneritida" pageId="1" pageNumber="190" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="moniliformis">
<emphasis box="[1068,1210,1596,1620]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="190">N. moniliformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Miocene of southwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[1022,1090,1622,1646]" name="France" pageId="1" pageNumber="190">France</collectingCountry>
, rather than 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[677,772,1648,1672]" class="Gastropoda" family="Neritopsidae" genus="Neritopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cycloneritida" pageId="1" pageNumber="190" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="radula">
<emphasis box="[677,772,1648,1672]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="190">N. radula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as was accepted in some monographs (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="MOORE R. C." box="[678,804,1675,1699]" pageId="1" pageNumber="190" refId="ref4924" refString="MOORE R. C. (ed.) 1960. - Treatise on Invertebrate Paleontology. Part I. Mollusca 1, Gastropoda. The Geological Society of America, University of Kansas Press, Lawrence, 351 p." type="book" year="1960">Moore 1960</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
